<section class="nwye-care">
  <div class="nwye-care-hero">
    <p class="nwye-eyebrow">Care Guide</p>
    <h1>Burn it right.<br>Keep it longer.</h1>
    <p class="nwye-intro">
      A few simple gestures to get the best from your candle — and from the object that remains.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="nwye-care-grid">
    <article class="nwye-care-card">
      <span>01</span>
      <h2>First Burn</h2>
      <h3>Let it melt properly.</h3>
      <p>Allow the entire surface of the wax to melt to the edges on the first use. This prevents tunneling and ensures an even burn over time.</p>
      <p class="nwye-note">Allow 2–3 hours minimum.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="nwye-care-card">
      <span>02</span>
      <h2>Trim the Wick</h2>
      <h3>Keep it clean.</h3>
      <p>Before each burn, trim the wick to around 5 mm. This maintains a steady flame, reduces smoke, and extends the life of your candle.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="nwye-care-card">
      <span>03</span>
      <h2>Burn Time</h2>
      <h3>Don’t rush it.</h3>
      <p>Burn your candle for a maximum of 3–4 hours at a time. Longer burns can overheat the wax and affect performance.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="nwye-care-card">
      <span>04</span>
      <h2>After Use</h2>
      <h3>Let it rest.</h3>
      <p>Extinguish with a snuffer — never blow or use water. Let the wax fully cool before moving the candle. Re-center the wick if needed.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="nwye-care-card">
      <span>05</span>
      <h2>When to Stop</h2>
      <h3>Know when it’s done.</h3>
      <p>Stop using your candle when approximately 10 mm of wax remains. This prevents overheating of the container.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="nwye-care-card">
      <span>06</span>
      <h2>Keep it Clean</h2>
      <h3>A better burn every time.</h3>
      <p>Keep the wax surface free of dust and debris. A clean candle burns better and smells better — always.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div class="nwye-care-bottom">
    <div class="nwye-rules">
      <p class="nwye-eyebrow">Burn Smart</p>
      <h2>A few simple rules.</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Burn on a heat-resistant surface</li>
        <li>Keep away from drafts</li>
        <li>Keep away from flammable objects</li>
        <li>Never leave unattended</li>
        <li>Keep away from children & pets</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="nwye-after">
